.panel.panel-color.panel-warning
  .panel-heading
    .panel-title
      Access to your Bitbucket account was denied!
  .panel-body
    %h3
      It seems that you need to re-authorise Testributor to access your Bitbucket
      account.
    %p
      There are two possible explanations for this:
    %p
      %ol
        %li
          You have manually revoked access to the Testributor OAuth application
          from your
          -# TODO We need to raise/rescue our own exception in order to pass
          -# additional information and correctly construct the following URL.
          #{link_to 'Bitbucket Settings', 'https://bitbucket.org/account', target: '_blank'}.
        %li
          The action you just attempted requires you to approve additional
          Bitbucket permissions for Testributor.
    %p
      = link_to "Authorize access", bitbucket_oauth_authorize_url, class: 'btn btn-raised btn-primary'
